=== Optional GPU Allocator Notes ===
include/memory_pool/gpu_allocator.hpp provides optional CUDA helpers.
They are compiled only when MEMORY_POOL_ENABLE_CUDA is defined.
Device memory is not ordinary host memory, so do not use cudaMalloc memory
as a normal std::vector backing store. Use CudaManagedVector<T> only with
CUDA unified memory, or use CudaDeviceBuffer<T> for kernel-facing buffers.
